<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Months. 2 months in one painting in Metrop[olitan] Mus[eum] New York, by a [onderstreept] Follower of Watteau, Metropol[itan] Mus[eum] Art. C. [Charles] Sterling, A Catalogue of French Paintings XV- XVIII Century [in the Metropolitan Museum of Art, Cambridge, MA: Metropolitan Museum of Art, Harvard University Press], 1955, pp. 108-112 (always with signs of zodiac): 22.225.6 Jan. & Feb.; 22.225.4 March & April; (no numbers: should probably be 22.225.2?) May & June; 22.225.1 July & August; 22.225.3 Sept. & Oct; 22.225.5 Nov. & Dec.; Detailed description each time in addition to decorative framework & zodiac signs, 2 separate scenes.</parts.title>

<parts.title>[Briefhoofd The Burrell Collection, Glasgow] Korte inhoud: Zending foto's van tapijten (Januari, April, September) uit The Burrell Collection, Glasgow. Heeft geen informatie over herkomst. Verwijst naar de tentoonstelling in Glasgow 1901 waar ze te zien waren in de collectie van Sir William Burrell, [= Glasgow International Exhibition, 1901]</parts.title>
<parts.title>3 zw/w foto's Januari, April, September uit The Burrell Collection, Glasgow.</parts.title>
